## Decision Log (Updated)

| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives Considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-02-04 | Multi-region KMS over regional | DR without key sync complexity | Create new key per region |
| 2026-02-04 | DynamoDB circuit breaker over SSM | Atomic operations, no race conditions | SSM (simpler but races), Redis (overkill) |
| 2026-02-04 | S3 backup over Global Tables | Simpler, cheaper, adequate RPO for 48h SLA | Global Tables (more complex) |
| 2026-02-04 | Remove WAF for private API | Cost/benefit ratio poor for internal API | Keep WAF (unnecessary cost) |
| 2026-02-04 | Versioned salt format | Enables rotation without data loss | Single salt (rotation = data loss) |
| 2026-02-04 | Relaxed durability SLO | 99.999% impractical at low volume | Keep 99.999% (unrealistic) |

